  "prompt": "What is the procedure to apply abroad for a masters in animation and graphic designing in US having done a 3 year bachelor degree in India?",
  "response": "To apply for a Master's in Animation and Graphic Design in the US with a 3-year bachelor's degree from India, follow these steps:\n\n1. Educational Equivalency\n- Get your 3-year degree evaluated by agencies like WES (World Education Services)\n- Obtain an equivalency certificate to a 4-year US bachelor's degree\n\n2. Academic Requirements\n- Maintain a good academic score (typically 60-65% or higher)\n- Strong portfolio showcasing design and animation skills\n\n3. Standardized Tests\n- Take GRE (recommended but not always mandatory)\n- TOEFL or IELTS for English proficiency\n- Minimum scores:\n  - TOEFL: 80-90 (internet-based)\n  - IELTS: 6.5-7.0\n\n4. Application Process\n- Research universities offering animation/graphic design programs\n- Check specific program requirements\n- Prepare:\n  - Statement of Purpose\n  - Letters of recommendation\n  - Portfolio\n  - Academic transcripts\n  - Passport\n  - Financial documents\n\n5. Funding Options\n- University scholarships\n- Educational loans\n- External scholarships\n- Assistantships\n\n6. Visa Process\n- Apply for I-20 form\n- Pay SEVIS fee\n- Schedule US visa interview\n\nRecommended universities:\n- School of Visual Arts, NY\n- Rhode Island School of Design\n- California Institute of the Arts\n- Savannah College of Art and Design",
